article.description: Nick McGlynn had 19 points and 11 rebounds and Drake built a big first-half lead to beat Bradley 69-52 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Drake builds big first-half lead to beat Bradley 69-52
article.linkText: Drake builds big first-half lead to beat Bradley 69-52
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Nick McGlynn had 19 points and 11 rebounds and Drake built a big first-half lead to beat Bradley 69-52 on Wednesday night. Drake (13-5, 2/3 Missouri Valley Conference) has defeated the Braves (8-10, 0-5) in three of the last four meetings. The Bulldogs closed the first half on a 26-6 run for a 33-15 advantage at the break. Brady Ellingson made three 3-pointers during the surge. Tremell Murphy scored eight of his 11 points in the first half and finished with a career-high 11 rebounds. Ellingson had 15 points and D.J. Wilkins chipped in with 10. Elijah Childs had 15 points and a career-best 13 rebounds to lead Bradley. The Braves shot just 19 of 61 (31 percent) from the field that included 12 missed 3-pointers while Drake was 26-of-50 shooting (52 percent). Dwayne Lautier-Ogunleye added 13 points and Luqman Lundy had 10 for the Braves.
